  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison is anxious to see Elizabeth Pease Nichol. He tells about his grandchildren. He gives his itinerary. Garrison writes: &quot;I believe it is the intention of some in London to proffer me a public breakfast, John Bright to preside on the occasion; and to that I shall not demur, as it will partake of a social character.&quot; He heard that Paris &quot;has been largely recreated within the last twelve years by the Emperor Napoleon.&quot;</subfield>
